		<element name="Mariner’s Armor" type="Magic Item" source="Dungeon Master’s Guide" id="ID_WOTC_DMG_MAGIC_ITEM_MARINERS_ARMOR">
			<description>
				<p>While wearing this armor, you have a swimming speed equal to your walking speed. In addition, whenever you start your turn underwater with 0 hit points, the armor causes you to rise 60 feet toward the surface. The armor is decorated with fish and shell motifs.</p>
			</description>
			<setters>
				<set name="category">Magic Armor</set>
				<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
				<set name="slot">body</set>
				<set name="type" addition="light, medium, or heavy">Armor</set>
				<set name="rarity">Uncommon</set>
				<set name="armor">ID_INTERNAL_ARMOR_GROUP_LIGHT||ID_INTERNAL_ARMOR_GROUP_MEDIUM||ID_INTERNAL_ARMOR_GROUP_HEAVY</set>
				<set name="name-format">Mariner’s {{parent}}</set>
			</setters>
			<rules>
				<stat name="speed:swim" value="speed" bonus="base" />
			</rules>
		</element>
		<element name="Mithral Armor" type="Magic Item" source="Dungeon Master’s Guide" id="ID_WOTC_DMG_MAGIC_ITEM_MITHRAL_ARMOR">
			<description>
				<p>Mithral is a light, flexible metal. A mithral chain shirt or breastplate can be worn under normal clothes. If the armor normally imposes disadvantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks or has a Strength requirement, the mithral version of the armor doesn't.</p>
			</description>
			<setters>
				<set name="keywords">medium, heavy</set>
				<set name="category">Magic Armor</set>
				<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
				<set name="slot">body</set>
				<set name="type" addition="medium or heavy, but not hide">Armor</set>
				<set name="rarity">Uncommon</set>
				<set name="armor">(ID_INTERNAL_ARMOR_GROUP_MEDIUM||ID_INTERNAL_ARMOR_GROUP_HEAVY),!Hide</set>
			</setters>
			<rules>
				<!-- todo: no disadvantage or strength requirement -->
			</rules>
		</element>
